Quote:  He swung the last box of coal round on to the rails and pushed it up the incline, trundling it along the unevenly fixed rails while his mate stayed to fix the jig - which controlled the boxes going to and from the coal-face fifteen feet above them at the side of the rails. <i>Ibid.</i> 420 box: A metal truck used in coal-mines.
